latestIgtvVideos.title: Nude Makeup using Bronzer & Highlighter
MINIMAL MAKEUP 💥
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Why to give a damn about what everyone thinks of your real skin? Everyone has flaws, no one is perfect. Makeup is not about transforming your whole facial features in order to what Society calls 'perfect'. It's about enhancing the beauty which already lies within you! 
Hiding "imperfections" is not the goal, it's about making yourself comfortable with them, so you don't feel like you have to cover them.
After all, us women dress up and do makeup to feel good, not to impress someone.😉
Happy women's Day!
__________________________

Read 👇🏻

Doing skincare is only gonna benefit you if you are also following it up with a good sunscreen

why you ask:

-Blocks harmful rays: Sunscreen protects your skin from UV rays that can cause damage.

-Prevents sunburn: Sunburns are painful and increase your risk of skin cancer.

-Slows aging: Sunscreen helps prevent wrinkles, sunspots, and other signs of premature aging.

-Keeps skin healthy: Sunscreen helps maintain even skin tone and prevents sun damage.

and so to sum it up, sunscreen is a shield that keeps your skin healthy and protected from the sun’s harmful effects.

And not just that, it’s also necessary to reapply because:

-Sunscreen wears off, it breaks down from sun exposure and rubs off from sweat, wate or clothes.
-Protection fades
- Gaps happen as t’s easy to miss some spots when applying
